The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Karat call

 Hyderabad June 24: The CPM has urged the Centre to accept the recommendations of the anti-terror acts review committee to hand over investigations into the Godhra train blaze and the communal violence that followed to the CBI.

 CPM general secretary Prakash Karat asked the UPA government to follow the Supreme Courts suggestions and foil attempts of the Gujarat government to circumvent procedures in the case and delay investigations.




